reviews.text: Tasting menu just the perfect amount!  Service was great, not feeling rushed. The meet was cooked to perfection! Loved everything.
Phenomenal steak. Great wine. Not too expensive (relative to Hong Kong prices). The street food snacks were also amazing too. Will return next time I am over!
Amazing food and fabulous wine list. Possibly the best steak of my life.

Food is amazing! Steaks were so tender and the entree (tartare and scallops!!) were perfect. Unfortunately we went to the rooftop for a drink after dinner and the restaurants F&B Director decided to take a phone call standing 5 metres away from us and shouting into his phone for 30 mins...totally ruined the atmosphere...well done for letting your team down! Would have been a higher score otherwise.

I was skeptical, but it was literally amazing. Flat Iron steak took 35 minutes to cook (they warned me in advance.) No idea what they did in that time, but ill wait again any time. Jalapeno mash potatoes phenomenal. Asparagus very good. And the chocolate souffle was incredible. The price was actually not bad having paid just as much at other places in Soho for inferior food. Highly recommend.
